Reading each out, fewer or some I'd 20 milligrams mornings, less than a pearl 10 milligrams daily, metaprolol tartrate 25 milligrams twice daily. A tower statin 20 milligrams nightly, metformin 500 milligrams twice daily with meals. Insulin glycine 10 units at bedtime. A pixaban 5 milligrams twice daily. Azithromycin, finished, albuterol inhaler as needed, acetaminophen 500 milligrams as needed. Iberprofen 200 milligrams as needed. How often, multivitamin daily, ginkgo biloba, how long, finished the antibiotic, I take Iberprofen sometimes for my knee. Ginkgo about a year, since you're on a pixaban, Iberprofen and ginkgo can increase bleeding risk. I recommend stopping ginkgo in avoiding Iberprofen. Use acetaminophen instead, I'll message your doctor, okay? Okay, I'll stop. For Insulin, do you check blood sugar? Mornings before breakfast, usually 110 to 140. No recent lows, great, keep logging those, I'll do a short memory screen. Repeat these three words, sock, blue, bed, sock, blue, bed, what year is it? 2025, month, August, day of the week, Saturday, and those three words again, sock, blue, bed, any recent confusion or sudden changes in attention? No, over the last two weeks. Little interest or pleasure in doing things? Maybe a little, not most days, feeling down or hopeless, not really, sleep okay, I wake up once or twice to use the bathroom. Pain today on 0 to 10? Right knee is a 3. We'll work on that with safer options given your blood thinner. For the next section, think about your usual performance over the last three days. Use whatever devices you normally use. Okay, eating, independent, oral hygiene, independent, toileting hygiene, I do it myself. Showering, bathing, I use a shower chair. My daughter stands by, supervision, upper body dressing, fine, lower body dressing in footwear, slower, but I can do it, shoelaces are annoying, bed mobility in transfers, okay, I push off arm rests, walking inside, with a cane, room to room, stairs, just the front stoop, two steps with a railing. Do you get short of breath with activity? Going from bedroom to kitchen. A bit, at rest, no, sleep with extra pillows, one extra, I'm seeing mild ankles swelling on both sides. Are you weighing daily, most mornings? Forgot yesterday, let's aim for daily, same scale, similar clothes, call if you gain two pounds in a day or five in a week. Or swelling worsens, got it, asterisk, daughter, Maya, arrives, asterisk, hi, Maya, I'm Rachel, we're reviewing safety, mind if we look around, go ahead, this throw rug can slip. Okay to remove or add non-slip backing, I'll roll it up, lighting is decent, a nightlight near the bathroom would help. Any grab bars, not yet, we recommend grab bars near the shower and toilet. Let's do a quick mobility test. Stand, walk ten feet with your cane. Turn, and sit at your usual pace. Ready, asterisk, patient completes, asterisk, that took 18 seconds, over approximately 12 to 14 seconds can mean higher fall risk. We'll add exercises, home mods, and request point, okay, any troubles following, no, appetite, fear, I get full fast, diet, low salt, watching carbs, bowel movements regular, every other day, any urine or stool accidents, I rush at night, no accidents, let me check your skin. Heels and tailbone look good, there's a small abrasion on your right shin. He bumped the coffee table last week, I'll clean it and place a small dressing, change it every other day. Or sooner if wet, I'll show you how, who lives with you, I live alone, Maya comes daily, a neighbor checks in, do you feel safe at home? Yes, any trouble getting to appointments? I drive him, any difficulty paying for meds or food? No, equipment at home, cane and shower chair, we'll add grab bars to the recommendations. Key heart failure points, daily morning weights, call if up 2 pounds per day or 5 pounds per week. Low salt diet, watch canned soups and deli meats. Meds per doctor guidance, we'll confirm with cardiology. Take meds as prescribed, don't skip diuretic, red flags, worsening breathlessness, swelling, needing more pillows, dizziness, chest pain, call 911 for severe chest pain. Because you're on a pixaban, avoid ibuprofen and herbals like ginkgo. Use acetaminophen for pain and call before starting new OTCs. Can you tell me the most important things you'll do this week? Way every morning, call if weight jumps, no ibuprofen or ginkgo, low salt, call 911 for serious chest pain or trouble breathing. Perfect, for the knee, stick to acetaminophen and wheel ad gentle exercises. I'll request physical therapy, plan of care, skilled nursing twice weekly for 2 weeks. Then weekly for 2, monitor weight, swelling, lungs, meds, and the shin wound, reinforce heart failure education, physical therapy twice weekly for balance, endurance, and safe walking, possible OT for energy conservation and shower safety. We'll send your doctor a summary today. Here's our 24-7 number. Call us about red flags. Call 911 for emergencies. Sounds good, I'll dispose of the ginkgo in label the ibuprofen, do not use. On blood thinner, we'll confirm fluid limits at your cardiology visit. Does Tuesday at 10am work for the next visit? Yes, we'll be here.
